Gunmen on Wednesday night killed an hotelier Falola Oke at Ilesha, Osun State. Oke, who is the Chief Executive Officer of Falola Hotel and Rental Service, was reportedly killed beside his house. The Nation gathered Oke, a father of six was killed around 9pm around Fadahunsi street, Imon area of Ilesha. When contacted, spokesperson of Osun Police Command, Mrs. Yemisi Opalola confirmed the incident. She said the Commissioner of Police, Mr Undie Adie has ordered investigation into the matter.